The paper deals with image retrieval, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves using a deep network architecture to learn to decompose an input query image into its basic components of categorical and attribute information, which is a machine learning task (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the advantages of their approach against a set of well-established retrieval model baselines, which involves comparing and evaluating different models (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper involves using a continuous control parameter to mix the categorical and attribute information to target a specific point along the retrieval simplex, which involves optimization and control (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the proposed model on a dataset, which involves multimedia (cs.MM).
